<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   CNN said it is giving up the fight to prevent the
release of court transcripts of its Manuel Noriega prison tapes.
   U.S. District Judge William Hoeveler, ruling in favor of four
news organizations that demanded access to the transcripts, said
Tuesday they would be released today unless CNN appealed. On
Wednesday, CNN said it would not do so.
   ``CNN's main concern in opposing unsealing of the transcripts
has been to protect the integrity of agreements with sources,'' CNN
spokesman Steve Haworth said.
