in this novel situation,'' Hoeveler said.
   The Atlanta-based network agreed not to play any of the disputed
tapes until the Supreme Court rules. In return, Noriega's defense
delayed a request for contempt penalties of up to $300,000 per
broadcast against the network, and Hoeveler stayed his order that
CNN hand over seven disputed tapes to the court.
   CNN attorney Terry Bienstock said the network had the right to
